main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright, football-shaped object that could be seen between clouds for about 30 seconds on December 13, 1957 in Oak Harbor, Washington.
interesting points: The object was described as a parallel, bright object.
The report indicates that the object was likely a jet aircraft, but there was insufficient data to make a definitive evaluation.
The report mentions that there were several other aircraft in the vicinity at the time, but no unusual incidents were reported.
Efforts to obtain additional information about the sighting were unsuccessful.
The object was ultimately classified as unidentifiable.
witnesses: a civilian, possibly a former Navy chief now working as a taxi driver
photographs: yes, but no photographs are included in the report
